<HEAD>Fifteen Zulus Killed in Clan Battle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fifteen people were killed
when members of two Zulu clans fought with rifles and submachine
guns in a rural settlement in the KwaZulu tribal homeland, police
reported today.
   National police headquarters in Pretoria said the fight occurred
Sunday at Etimatola, near Pietermaritzburg in Natal Province.
   A police spokesman in Pietermaritzburg, Maj. Pieter Kitching,
said the cause of the clash was not known. There was no indication
it was related to the prolonged factional fighting in the region
between supporters of militant anti-apartheid groups and followers
of Inkatha, a more conservative Zulu organization.
   Kitching said the atmosphere in Etimatola was very tense.
   ``We have members of the riot unit on standby until we are
satisfied tempers have calmed down,'' he said.
