<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0428</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Strike South, Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Severe thunderstorms produced damaging winds and hail across
portions of the South and Midwest, and parts of Oklahoma were
contending with tornadoes.
   Two tornadoes touched down near Mangum and Elk City.
Baseball-size hail fell south of Bartlesville. No injuries or major
damage were reported.
   Thunderstorms and gusting winds also were reported in Texas and
in the southeast third of Kansas.
   Elsewhere, showers and thunderstorms were reported in Minnesota,
eastern South Dakota, western Iowa, eastern Nebraska, eastern
Kansas and western Missouri. Rain also was scattered over northeast
Colorado, northeast Ohio and the northern two-thirds of the Pacific
Coast.
   Snow fell over north-central North Dakota.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 1 a.m. EST
included 1.76 inches at Enid, Okla.; 1.45 inches at Oklahoma City;
and more than an inch at Topeka, Kan.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms along a
cold front that reached from the southern Plains and lower
Mississippi Valley across the Great Lakes and northern New England;
possible severe thunderstorms from central Texas and southeast
Oklahoma to Louisiana and Arkansas; rain from the northern and
central Pacific Coast to the northern Rockies; and gusty winds over
the northern Plains.
   Highs were to be in the 50s from northern California and the
northern Pacific Coast to Idaho, from northern Montana across
Minnesota to upper Michigan, northern Maine, and from northern
Arizona to southern Colorado; and in the 70s and 80s over the
desert Southwest, southern New England and from the southern Plains
to the southern and middle Atlantic Coast.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 27
degrees at Devils Lake, N.D., to 76 degrees at McAllen, Texas,
Miami and Homestead and Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 63 fair; Boston 52 cloudy; Buffalo 52 rain;
Charleston, S.C. 61 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 63 partly cloudy;
Cleveland 65 cloudy; Detroit 61 foggy; Miami 75 fair; New York 45
foggy; Philadelphia 54 foggy; Pittsburgh 64 fair; Portland, Maine
43 cloudy; Washington 60 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 33 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth 60
thunderstorms; Denver 40 fair; Des Moines 59 rain; Indianapolis 61
cloudy; Kansas City 58 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 43 foggy;
Nashville 63 fair; St. Louis 64 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 47 fair; Anchorage 22 windy; Las Vegas 54
fair; Los Angeles 55 fair; Phoenix 58 fair; Salt Lake City 43 fair;
San Diego 55 fair; San Francisco 56 cloudy; Seattle 41 partly
cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 50 fair; Toronto 55 foggy.
</TEXT>
