<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--Truck-DEA     03-28 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Truck-DEA,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Runs Over Police Car in Drug Buy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The driver of a big-wheeled truck
chased federal drug agents as they attempted to make a cocaine
bust, then used his high-riding vehicle to run over the hood of a
police car, authorities said Tuesday.
   Three men inside the truck Monday evening were arrested for
investigation of attempted murder and possession of drugs for sale,
Sgt. Bill Thompson said.
   No officers or agents were injured, he said, but one of the men
inside the truck was bitten by a police dog when he tried to
escape. The men were held at the Inglewood jail.
   Federal Drug Enforcement Administration agents had tried to
arrest the men after meeting them in a parking lot for a cocaine
buy, Thompson said. But the men fled in the four-wheel-drive
Chevrolet Blazer.
   ``The Blazer at one point drove over the top of one of our
unmarked cars,'' he said, ``just like you see at the Coliseum'' in
truck shows.
   Officers fired after the truck as it sped off and then then
crashed into a building.
</TEXT>
