   _Carol T. Crawford, an associate director of the White House
budget office, to be assistant attorney general for legislative
affairs. Ms. Crawford, 46, has worked in the federal government
since 1981 at the Federal Trade Commission and at the Office of
Management and Budget. If confirmed by the Senate, she would
succeed Thomas M. Boyd.
   _Roger Bolton, 38, as assistant secretary of the treasury for
public affairs, succeeding Edith E. Holiday. Since 1988, Bolton has
been special assistant to the president for public liaison and an
economic aide.
   _William G. Rosenberg to be assistant administrator for air and
radiation in the Environmental Protection Agency.
