<FIRST>r a AM-Oscars-Razzies     03-28 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oscars-Razzies,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sylvester Stallone, `Cocktail' Win Razzies for Hollywood's Worst</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sylvester Stallone was named worst actor and
``Cocktail'' was selected worst picture for 1988 top honors in the
Golden Raspberry Awards announced Tuesday.
   Other big Razzie winners (or losers) included Liza Minnelli for
worst actress (``Arthur 2: On the Rocks'' and ``Rent-a-Cop''), Dan
Aykroyd for worst supporting actor (``Caddyshack II'') and Kristy
McNichol for worst supporting actress (``Two-Moon Junction'').
   The Razzie statuettes are scheduled to be presented Wednesday
night by the Golden Raspberry Awards Foundation at a local
nightclub during commercial breaks of the Academy Awards telecast.
Recipients are not expected to be in attendance.
   Stallone's worst actor Razzie, given for his work in ``Rambo
III,'' was his third in only five years. He ``won'' in 1985 for
``Rhinestone'' and in 1986 for ``Rambo: First Blood Part II'' and
``Rocky IV.''
   Blake Edwards (``Sunset'') and Stewart Raffill (``Mac and Me'')
tied for worst director, ``Cocktail'' took worst screenplay and
hamburger pitchman Ronald McDonald was chosen worst new star for
playing himself in ``Mac and Me.''
   The Razzies are voted on by more than 200 publicists.
