   Authorities imposed a dusk-to-dawn
curfew in Kosovo after ethnic Albanians angered by encroachments on
their autonomy battled police in the worst violence in the southern
province since 1981.
   State-run news media said two policemen were shot and killed
Monday in two of the seven Kosovo towns where violent protests were
reported. Reports that two demonstrators also were killed could not
be confirmed.
   Authorities ordered a curfew from 8 p.m. to 5 a.m., banned any
