<HEAD>For Release Sunday, April 2, and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>AP SPOTLIGHT: Catholics in Africa _ Church at a Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: One of a package of four stories. With b0772-b0773.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some facts and figures on the Roman Catholic
Church in Africa, based on latest edition of the Statistical
Yearbook of the Church:
   _Number of Catholics in world: 850 million.
   _Number of Catholics in Africa: 75 million, 13 percent of total
population of 572 million.
   _Percentage of Catholics in Africa in 1900: 1 percent.
   _Projected number of African Catholics by 2000: 100 million, 18
percent of population.
   _The African clerical ranks: 17 cardinals, 481 bishops, 18,353
priests, 44,764 seminarians.
   _Catechists (religious teachers) _ 216,026.
</TEXT>
