<FILEID>AP-NR-03-28-89 0758EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-CondomExpirationDate     03-28 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Condom Expiration Date,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Makers of Latex Condoms Agree to Give Expiration Dates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Manufacturers of latex condoms in the United
States have agreed to provide expiration dates for their products,
The New York Times reported today.
   A spokesman for a trade group that represents condom makers said
a letter would be sent today to several New York legislators and
the U.S. Food and Drug Administration informing them of the
decision, the Times reported.
   The New York State Assembly passed a bill earlier this month
that would require manufacturers to give expiration dates for
condoms.
   The letter from the Health Industry Manufacturers Association
asks that the state Senate take no action on the bill since
manufacturers have agreed to the requirement.
   Norman Estrin, vice president of science and technology for the
association, told the Times that manufacturers would individually
determine an expiration date for their products.
   The issue of expiration dates has taken on increased importance
among legislators and consumer activists as more people turn to
condoms for protection against sexually transmitted diseases.
</TEXT>
