<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing stock prices.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed higher Tuesday on the London
Stock Exchange, as trading resumed after a four-day Easter holiday
and the market awaited the British trade report for February.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was up 13.5 points, or 0.7 percent, at 2,070.5.
   Volume was a scant 342.8 million shares, compared with 407.8
million shares on the previous trading day last Thursday.
   Equities got off to a strong start on the back of gains earlier
on Tuesday in Tokyo, where the Nikkei index jumped almost 800
points to 32,306.36.
   But the upward move couldn't be sustained Tuesday afternoon,
despite renewed rises in early Wall Street business. Dealers said
apprehension ahead of Wednesday's trade report pulled prices down
from their best levels.
   The Financial Times 30-share index was up 9.6 points at 1,708.0
at the close. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 7.14 points
to close 1,180.44.
