<HEAD>Picks New Head for Trade Panel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush promoted Anne E. Brunsdale on
Tuesday to be chairman of the Commerce Department's International
Trade Commission.
   She has been a member of the commission since 1985 and vice
chairman since June 16, 1986. She replaces Susan Wittenberg Liebler.
   To fill the vice chairman's slot, Bush picked Ronald A. Cass, a
member for a little more than a year.
   The commission hears trade complaints from U.S. manufacturers.
